1
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:02,160
You just show up with a letter?

2
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:03,800
How do we know you're the real one?

3
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:07,080
<i>Help! A thief!</i>

4
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:09,320
Let go!

5
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:12,320
That arrogant guy you were badmouthing

6
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:13,840
is your uncle?

7
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:16,280
Talk about a small world.

8
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:18,560
And now we're stuck
living under the same roof.

9
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:20,360
Uncle Ree?

10
00:02:21,720 --> 00:02:23,680
What on earth are you doing?

11
00:02:24,920 --> 00:02:26,360
I promise

12
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:29,720
I'll guard your fortune with my life.

13
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:31,720
I'm on an official mission

14
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:33,320
to take down Zhang Gong Cheng.

15
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:35,320
<i>He's a pirate who terrorizes</i>
<i>the ships in these waters,</i>

16
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:36,680
<i>leaving nothing but ruin in his wake.</i>

17
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:38,680
What does that have to do with this house?

18
00:02:40,640 --> 00:02:41,760
Help us!

19
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:42,920
Uncle Ree!

20
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:48,840
ADISUAN LUMBER

21
00:02:56,480 --> 00:02:58,360
Are these for me?

22
00:03:00,440 --> 00:03:03,440
Yes, dear. If not for you,
then who else would I give them to?

23
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:05,440
Thank you.

24
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,880
You're doing a great job
with the accounts.

25
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:15,880
Just like the last time you helped me.

26
00:03:17,920 --> 00:03:20,440
But didn't you say
you disliked it before, Auntie?

27
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:23,880
Well, you know how it is.

28
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:30,480
I just don't trust that…

29
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:35,560
I mean, Thatri.

30
00:03:36,160 --> 00:03:39,800
All day long, I see him just
wandering around, chatting with everyone.

31
00:03:39,880 --> 00:03:42,560
He hasn't done anything.

32
00:03:42,640 --> 00:03:45,800
I doubt he could handle
the business as well as you do.

33
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:12,520
From now on, Mr. Thatri,

34
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:14,800
you must read every single detail.

35
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:16,240
Don't let anything slip past you.

36
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:21,880
Why? I thought Uncle Som's kin
were handling things.

37
00:04:22,520 --> 00:04:23,560
Honestly,

38
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:26,600
I don't trust anyone in this family.

39
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:28,080
It's obvious they're all
just after the inheritance.

40
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:31,560
Is it that serious?
What exactly are they after?

41
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:35,320
You've seen their true colors
yourself, Mr. Thatri.

42
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:37,360
Especially Miss Paetai.

43
00:04:38,360 --> 00:04:41,800
Her tongue is so sharp,
I wouldn't dare cross her.

44
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:44,960
And what about the others?

45
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:46,600
There's Miss Fuangfah.

46
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:49,680
She's Miss Paetai's younger sister.
Neither of them can be trusted.

47
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:52,880
As for Auntie Jiam,
the housekeeper you met,

48
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:55,800
she guards Mr. Som's assets like a hawk.

49
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:09,480
ADISUAN PEARLS

50
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:13,360
You know, you should be
the one inheriting everything.

51
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:20,640
- What makes you say that, Auntie?
- I'm just worried, dear.

52
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:23,680
I'm afraid Thatri
won't be able to manage it,

53
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:25,960
since he's never worked here before.

54
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,080
That's true.

55
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:33,240
Let's just wait and see for now.

56
00:05:33,840 --> 00:05:36,320
I just hope he doesn't sell
the inheritance off,

57
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:40,640
considering Uncle Som
built all of this from the ground up.

58
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:21,520
What's with the attitude?

59
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:24,160
Why the need to slam things around?

60
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:26,280
Come here.

61
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:28,160
What is it?

62
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:32,160
I said, come here.

63
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:45,640
Nid told me you refused
to clean your wound,

64
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:48,160
so he asked me to come and do it for you.

65
00:06:50,760 --> 00:06:51,960
I'm alright.

66
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:54,440
I'd rather get back to work.
There's so much to do.

67
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:57,320
Uncle Ree, you're a grown man,
not a child.

68
00:06:58,640 --> 00:06:59,920
Sit down.

69
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,480
And how is your work going?

70
00:07:57,920 --> 00:08:01,720
I left the mine and went to check
the accounts at the pearl company

71
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,600
and the agarwood company.

72
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:07,000
The rest will have to wait until tomorrow.

73
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:10,560
I have no idea how Grandpa Som

74
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:13,400
managed such a massive workload.

75
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:21,320
If it's exhausting, why not sell off
some of the companies?

76
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:26,560
You might burn yourself out.

77
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:35,840
I just don't trust that…

78
00:08:38,760 --> 00:08:40,400
I mean, Thatri.

79
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:44,640
All day long, I see him just
wandering around, chatting with everyone.

80
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:46,800
He hasn't done anything.

81
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:50,480
I doubt he could handle
the business as well as you do.

82
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,640
I'm just worried, dear.

83
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:56,960
I'm afraid Thatri
won't be able to manage it,

84
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:59,240
since he's never worked here before.

85
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:01,680
Let's just wait and see for now.

86
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:04,920
I just hope he doesn't sell
the inheritance off,

87
00:09:05,560 --> 00:09:09,400
considering Uncle Som
built all of this from the ground up.

88
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:15,000
Everything my grandfather
worked so hard to build,

89
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:17,200
I won't just sell it off.

90
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:18,720
I'm not like you, Uncle Ree.

91
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:20,240
What's that supposed to mean?

92
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:24,360
Well, isn't it true?
That's what everyone is saying,

93
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:27,440
if you get the inheritance,
you'll just sell it all off.

94
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:32,640
I don't trust anyone in this family.

95
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:34,440
It's clear they're all
after the inheritance.

96
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:39,120
Who told you that?
Whoever said it doesn't mean well.

97
00:09:40,880 --> 00:09:43,440
I only suggested selling
because I'm worried about you.

98
00:09:44,040 --> 00:09:46,640
Even for me, this is a lot to handle.

99
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:52,080
For a woman like you, keeping
just one of these, you'd be set for life.

100
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,800
Ouch! Hey!

101
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:01,200
Are you trying to heal me or rip me apart?

102
00:10:03,880 --> 00:10:05,480
Finish it yourself.

103
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:15,840
What's her problem?

104
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:24,440
Talk about a mood swing.

105
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:26,480
I was just trying to help.

106
00:10:33,560 --> 00:10:35,000
Hey, Don Jose.

107
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:39,600
Do you know your mom
just snapped at Dad for no reason?

108
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:44,080
Dad?

109
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:47,680
Do you know your mom
just snapped at me for no reason?

110
00:10:47,760 --> 00:10:50,600
I was worried because of her workload
and feared she'd get exhausted.

111
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:52,640
I don't get

112
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:54,320
why she's making such a fuss.

113
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:58,640
You're on my side, right, boy?

114
00:10:59,680 --> 00:11:01,640
I knew you'd agree.

115
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:03,600
Men understand each other.

116
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:05,680
Not like your mother.

117
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:09,840
She's the most difficult woman
in the world to understand.

118
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:13,320
Being with her is a lifelong headache.

119
00:12:01,920 --> 00:12:02,960
Uncle Ree?

120
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:21,680
If someone sees you,
we're gonna get problems.

121
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,520
I understand.

122
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:29,240
You could've told me you speak Thai.
What happened?

123
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:30,720
How did you get hurt?

124
00:12:31,560 --> 00:12:35,200
I was shot by Japanese soldiers.

125
00:12:38,040 --> 00:12:39,040
You know, right?

126
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:42,040
Japan is at war with America.

127
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:44,560
Bringing an American soldier
into the house is extremely risky.

128
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:48,600
I know, but I found him injured out front.

129
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:50,240
Was I supposed to do nothing?

130
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:51,960
If the Japanese find out,

131
00:12:52,040 --> 00:12:53,760
we'll all be in deep trouble.

132
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:56,600
We must get him out of here immediately,

133
00:12:56,680 --> 00:12:57,600
before anyone sees.

134
00:12:58,320 --> 00:13:01,480
We can't. Mr. Michael is severely injured.

135
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:03,440
I'm letting him rest here for now.

136
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,640
If they find out,

137
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:09,560
we'll all be dead meat.
I'm not going down with you.

138
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:11,520
Mr. Thatri!

139
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:14,160
Mr. Thatri!

140
00:13:14,880 --> 00:13:15,920
Mr. Thatri.

141
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:20,280
Nid, how did you know I was here?

142
00:13:20,880 --> 00:13:23,520
No time for questions.
The Japanese are at the house right now.

143
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:25,480
Huh?

144
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:48,640
Colonel Nakamura.

145
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:53,200
What brings you here today?

146
00:13:53,280 --> 00:13:57,000
I've been informed that someone
in the Som Song Saeng house

147
00:13:57,080 --> 00:13:59,480
is harboring an American soldier.

148
00:13:59,560 --> 00:14:01,520
I must search the premises.

149
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:04,120
My apologies.

150
00:14:12,640 --> 00:14:15,960
What is going on? Why are there
Japanese soldiers in our house?

151
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:18,440
Exactly.

152
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:22,520
Colonel Nakamura received a tip

153
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:25,600
that an American soldier
is being hidden here,

154
00:14:25,680 --> 00:14:26,960
so he's conducting a search.

155
00:14:29,240 --> 00:14:31,560
Feel free to look around.
I'll show you the way.

156
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:35,560
There's a specific area
I'd like you to see.

157
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:38,360
This way, please.

158
00:14:49,280 --> 00:14:51,080
Ugh, what a mess.

159
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:53,880
It's been chaotic
since that outsider moved in.

160
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:11,600
There's one more place
I haven't shown you.

161
00:15:11,680 --> 00:15:14,680
I've been meaning
to have you check it out anyway.

162
00:15:15,360 --> 00:15:17,560
I heard some strange noises
coming from there.

163
00:15:34,880 --> 00:15:35,720
Everyone, get ready!

164
00:15:38,160 --> 00:15:40,040
- Lead the way.
- Yes, sir.

165
00:15:48,760 --> 00:15:50,000
This is the place, Colonel.

166
00:15:55,560 --> 00:15:57,400
Is anyone inside?

167
00:16:31,120 --> 00:16:33,320
He's not here. Could he have escaped?

168
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:35,120
You might still catch him, Colonel.

169
00:16:36,840 --> 00:16:38,160
Spread out! Hunt him down!

170
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:39,640
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

171
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:49,440
- So it was you, Nid.
- Yes, madam.

172
00:16:51,680 --> 00:16:54,400
- Please take your medicine first, sir.
- Thank you.

173
00:17:01,160 --> 00:17:02,600
Are you alright, Miss Rajit?

174
00:17:02,680 --> 00:17:04,400
I was terrified.

175
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:07,680
When you opened that door,
I thought it was the Japanese soldiers.

176
00:17:07,760 --> 00:17:09,440
I really thought we were done for.

177
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:13,079
I'm sorry for giving you a fright.

178
00:17:13,160 --> 00:17:16,480
I was rushing to follow Mr. Thatri's plan.
I didn't have a moment to let you know.

179
00:17:20,319 --> 00:17:21,160
Nid,

180
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:23,839
take the first-aid kit
to the injured man at the hut.

181
00:17:23,920 --> 00:17:26,920
Make sure no one sees you.
I'll lead the Japanese soldiers away.

182
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,640
But that's too risky, Mr. Thatri.

183
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:32,520
I have a plan.
If I'm the one providing the lead,

184
00:17:33,120 --> 00:17:35,000
Colonel Nakamura won't suspect a thing.

185
00:17:35,080 --> 00:17:36,960
I'll lead him to a different hut,

186
00:17:37,040 --> 00:17:38,240
not the one where Rajit is.

187
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:40,200
Just make sure you don't mess up.

188
00:17:40,280 --> 00:17:41,400
Understood.

189
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:48,800
Mr. Thatri is really quick-witted.

190
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:51,240
If not for his help, we'd be done for.

191
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:53,520
Uncle Ree…

192
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:03,680
I'm truly sorry

193
00:18:03,760 --> 00:18:05,400
I couldn't do more for you.

194
00:18:06,040 --> 00:18:07,680
This is more than enough.

195
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:12,120
If the Japanese found out
you helped a spy like me,

196
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:13,680
you'd be in grave danger.

197
00:18:14,600 --> 00:18:18,440
I'm truly in your debt.

198
00:18:19,320 --> 00:18:21,560
Michael, I'll have Nid

199
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:24,400
escort you on a boat
until you reach your ship.

200
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:26,040
Thank you.

201
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:28,760
Be careful, Nid.

202
00:18:28,840 --> 00:18:29,680
I will.

203
00:18:30,560 --> 00:18:31,800
Let's go, Mr. Michael.

204
00:18:55,880 --> 00:18:56,760
What are you staring at?

205
00:18:56,840 --> 00:18:59,040
It's you. Why are you looking at me?

206
00:18:59,760 --> 00:19:01,680
I have things on my mind.
I wasn't looking at you.

207
00:19:02,720 --> 00:19:04,600
I have things to think about too.

208
00:19:04,680 --> 00:19:05,880
But mine is important.

209
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,480
So are mine.

210
00:19:08,560 --> 00:19:09,760
What's on your mind then?

211
00:19:10,760 --> 00:19:12,560
You tell me yours first, Uncle Ree.

212
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:17,880
Colonel Nakamura arrived far too quickly.

213
00:19:18,720 --> 00:19:19,680
How did he even know

214
00:19:19,760 --> 00:19:22,080
Michael was hiding
at Som Song Saeng House?

215
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:24,080
Do you think someone

216
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:27,320
is using Michael to target us?

217
00:19:28,240 --> 00:19:29,280
Maybe.

218
00:19:30,360 --> 00:19:32,360
But I can't put my finger on anyone.

219
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:35,800
I've told you mine. Now, it's your turn.

220
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:39,240
Your English
is incredibly fluent, Uncle Ree.

221
00:19:50,880 --> 00:19:54,640
Your English is far too good
for a high school graduate.

222
00:19:55,240 --> 00:19:57,560
Even after studying in Penang,

223
00:19:57,640 --> 00:19:58,840
mine isn't as good as yours.

224
00:20:00,480 --> 00:20:02,680
You sound like someone who's lived abroad.

225
00:20:03,560 --> 00:20:05,360
That's nonsense.

226
00:20:05,440 --> 00:20:07,960
How could someone like me
afford to study abroad?

227
00:20:08,560 --> 00:20:11,240
I told you, I used to mow lawns
at a wealthy estate.

228
00:20:11,320 --> 00:20:13,240
I just picked up
a few things along the way.

229
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:16,640
Which household was that?

230
00:20:16,720 --> 00:20:19,800
You certainly picked up a lot.
First, it was opera,

231
00:20:19,880 --> 00:20:21,640
and now it's fluent English.

232
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:28,160
Hey, wait. Uncle Ree.

233
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:31,800
Uncle Ree, answer me first.
Don't you walk away from me.

234
00:20:31,880 --> 00:20:34,760
Hey. Uncle Ree, stop walking away.

235
00:20:35,880 --> 00:20:37,680
Why are you avoiding me?

236
00:20:37,760 --> 00:20:39,520
You haven't answered me yet.

237
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:42,120
- It's nothing.
- If you don't answer me today,

238
00:20:43,160 --> 00:20:44,880
I'm not going to let you off the hook.

239
00:21:28,800 --> 00:21:30,960
- What's this?
- It's O-aew.

240
00:21:35,520 --> 00:21:39,040
It's called O-aew.
It's a local Phuket dessert.

241
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:41,800
If the name is too complicated for you,

242
00:21:41,880 --> 00:21:43,400
you don't have to memorize it.

243
00:21:44,160 --> 00:21:45,040
I've got it.

244
00:21:45,880 --> 00:21:47,920
I've never heard of it before, that's all.

245
00:22:02,200 --> 00:22:03,160
This is delicious.

246
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:05,760
Does Phuket really have food this good?

247
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:09,240
Yes. Actually, O-aew

248
00:22:09,320 --> 00:22:11,440
originated from the Hokkien Chinese.

249
00:22:11,520 --> 00:22:13,960
It became so popular in Phuket

250
00:22:14,040 --> 00:22:16,600
that it's now a local staple.

251
00:22:17,280 --> 00:22:21,240
In Penang, they call it Bun Thau Bee.

252
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:25,200
I loved it so much
when I was studying there,

253
00:22:25,280 --> 00:22:26,920
so I practiced making it.

254
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:28,400
You made this yourself?

255
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:30,480
I assumed you bought it.

256
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:37,560
I made this

257
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:40,760
to thank you for helping me.

258
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:44,200
But if you don't want it,

259
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:45,880
you don't have to eat it.

260
00:22:45,960 --> 00:22:47,920
I'd be a fool not to eat
something this delicious.

261
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:04,280
Jiam, is something the matter?

262
00:23:04,880 --> 00:23:06,520
I have no business with you.

263
00:23:07,520 --> 00:23:09,720
I have something to tell Mr. Thatri.

264
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:11,880
Me? What is it?

265
00:23:12,640 --> 00:23:14,760
It's about the warning I gave you.

266
00:23:19,720 --> 00:23:21,720
Why should I give up the inheritance?

267
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:23,560
This is a blatant threat.

268
00:23:23,640 --> 00:23:25,720
Yes. I'm threatening you

269
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:29,920
because you never belonged
to the Adisuan family in the first place.

270
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:32,160
I don't owe you any respect.

271
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:34,720
Now, get out.

272
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:36,440
Isn't that a bit too easy, Paetai?

273
00:23:37,240 --> 00:23:39,240
I received this inheritance
legally through the will.

274
00:23:39,320 --> 00:23:40,720
The lawyer is right here.

275
00:23:40,800 --> 00:23:42,520
He's the one who sent for me.

276
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:45,560
You can't just use
your thick skin to kick me out.

277
00:23:45,640 --> 00:23:46,640
Mmh!

278
00:23:46,720 --> 00:23:48,280
- You bastard!
- Pae…

279
00:23:48,360 --> 00:23:50,640
I told you this wouldn't work,
but you wouldn't listen.

280
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:52,400
Why not?

281
00:23:52,480 --> 00:23:54,600
Uncle Som only left him the inheritance

282
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:56,960
because he believes you're the grandson,

283
00:23:57,040 --> 00:23:58,240
but he's not.

284
00:23:58,320 --> 00:24:00,600
His mother was the product of an affair.

285
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:03,280
He doesn't have a single drop
of Adisuan blood in him.

286
00:24:03,360 --> 00:24:05,360
How can he just snatch the fortune?

287
00:24:05,440 --> 00:24:08,120
Exactly. How can a complete stranger

288
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:09,640
just walk away with the fortune?

289
00:24:11,160 --> 00:24:14,120
At least we're related
to Uncle Som's wife.

290
00:24:14,200 --> 00:24:17,280
For better or worse,
we have more of a connection to him

291
00:24:17,360 --> 00:24:19,400
than the child of some adulteress.

292
00:24:19,480 --> 00:24:21,800
And how do you all know

293
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:24,600
that Uncle Ree doesn't share
Grandpa Som's blood?

294
00:24:24,680 --> 00:24:26,480
All of you.

295
00:24:26,560 --> 00:24:30,320
Do you have any proof?
Any blood test results to back this up?

296
00:24:32,240 --> 00:24:33,440
You…

297
00:24:35,280 --> 00:24:36,600
How could we have that?

298
00:24:37,320 --> 00:24:39,800
Hey, this is the second time
you've taken his side.

299
00:24:39,880 --> 00:24:41,600
Whose side are you really on, Rajit?

300
00:24:41,680 --> 00:24:43,440
I'm not taking sides.

301
00:24:43,520 --> 00:24:45,520
I'm standing for what is right.

302
00:24:46,640 --> 00:24:48,520
You all can't just

303
00:24:48,600 --> 00:24:49,640
demand Uncle Ree

304
00:24:49,720 --> 00:24:53,120
to renounce his inheritance
without a shred of evidence.

305
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,240
That's correct.

306
00:24:54,840 --> 00:24:57,720
Mr. Thatri is the legal heir
according to the will.

307
00:24:57,800 --> 00:25:00,440
Even if there were no blood relation,

308
00:25:00,520 --> 00:25:02,600
the will remains legally binding.

309
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:04,040
- What?
- Ugh!

310
00:25:04,600 --> 00:25:05,600
Ugh!

311
00:25:07,120 --> 00:25:10,080
Fine then. We'll see you in court.

312
00:25:11,480 --> 00:25:12,920
We believe

313
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:15,200
if Uncle Som knew
you weren't his real grandson,

314
00:25:15,280 --> 00:25:18,400
he never would've made that will.

315
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:20,640
I have witnesses from back then.

316
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:25,400
I'll expose the truth and you'll want
to crawl back into the hole you came from.

317
00:25:25,480 --> 00:25:28,600
Then name the date. I'm ready.

318
00:25:30,520 --> 00:25:32,640
This inheritance means nothing to me

319
00:25:33,520 --> 00:25:34,880
compared to my dignity.

320
00:25:42,760 --> 00:25:44,840
<i>I was just acting tough.</i>

321
00:25:46,840 --> 00:25:49,200
<i>In reality, I have no idea</i>
<i>how to fight this,</i>

322
00:25:49,280 --> 00:25:50,960
<i>since I have no information.</i>

323
00:25:51,720 --> 00:25:53,040
<i>Do you have any evidence?</i>

324
00:25:53,880 --> 00:25:55,760
<i>I'll handle your relatives for you.</i>

325
00:26:03,920 --> 00:26:05,400
I feel so guilty.

326
00:26:09,240 --> 00:26:10,960
I shouldn't have sent you there.

327
00:26:12,360 --> 00:26:13,720
Leopard.

328
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:24,200
<i>Thank you for standing up for me.</i>

329
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:26,720
<i>But I am too ashamed</i>

330
00:26:27,320 --> 00:26:29,440
<i>to even speak of my mother's past.</i>

331
00:26:30,120 --> 00:26:31,960
<i>It's like a scar</i>

332
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:34,000
<i>that will never fade.</i>

333
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:36,960
<i>This didn't just happen.</i>

334
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:41,000
<i>It started the day she was born.</i>

335
00:26:41,760 --> 00:26:44,200
<i>My grandmother</i>
<i>was my grandfather's mistress.</i>

336
00:26:44,280 --> 00:26:48,080
<i>And my mother was born</i>
<i>six months after he passed.</i>

337
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:49,240
<i>All the relatives</i>

338
00:26:49,320 --> 00:26:52,400
<i>accused my grandmother of having an affair</i>

339
00:26:52,480 --> 00:26:53,920
<i>and refused to take my mother in.</i>

340
00:26:54,480 --> 00:26:56,560
Get out! You unfaithful wretch!

341
00:26:57,160 --> 00:26:58,240
Pack your bags and leave.

342
00:26:58,320 --> 00:27:00,240
Don't you set foot in this house again.

343
00:27:00,320 --> 00:27:01,640
Get lost.

344
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:02,640
Go.

345
00:27:02,720 --> 00:27:03,920
Get out!

346
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:04,960
Out now!

347
00:27:05,880 --> 00:27:06,760
Leave.

348
00:27:06,840 --> 00:27:08,000
Go!

349
00:27:09,240 --> 00:27:10,640
Get out.

350
00:27:24,880 --> 00:27:27,640
<i>My mother grew up surrounded by insults</i>

351
00:27:28,360 --> 00:27:30,240
<i>and endless bullying from those relatives.</i>

352
00:27:30,840 --> 00:27:32,120
<i>After my grandmother passed away,</i>

353
00:27:32,720 --> 00:27:35,680
<i>she moved from Phuket to Chiang Mai,</i>

354
00:27:35,760 --> 00:27:37,120
<i>where she finally met my father.</i>

355
00:27:38,360 --> 00:27:41,240
<i>By now, you must realize</i>

356
00:27:42,120 --> 00:27:43,920
<i>I have no evidence.</i>

357
00:27:44,560 --> 00:27:48,800
<i>If there were any, my mother would have</i>
<i>used it to reclaim her dignity long ago.</i>

358
00:27:50,880 --> 00:27:52,280
<i>As for the inheritance,</i>

359
00:27:53,120 --> 00:27:55,160
<i>I don't want you to suffer any further.</i>

360
00:27:55,800 --> 00:27:58,200
<i>If it's too much, just back out.</i>

361
00:27:59,040 --> 00:28:00,840
<i>I'm willing to give it all up.</i>

362
00:28:02,320 --> 00:28:03,560
Wild Bull…

363
00:28:06,840 --> 00:28:08,400
What bull are you talking about?

364
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:13,920
Spying on me? How rude.

365
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:15,360
You said it out loud.

366
00:28:15,440 --> 00:28:17,920
Don't blame me for hearing it.

367
00:28:18,600 --> 00:28:19,840
How fair of you.

368
00:28:23,080 --> 00:28:23,960
What do you want?

369
00:28:40,680 --> 00:28:41,640
For me?

370
00:28:43,400 --> 00:28:44,440
Yes.

371
00:28:45,040 --> 00:28:49,400
I also want to say,
don't let it get to you.

372
00:28:50,320 --> 00:28:53,280
Grandpa made that will for you.

373
00:28:53,360 --> 00:28:55,720
It was his final wish.

374
00:28:55,800 --> 00:28:58,040
No one else has the right to overrule it.

375
00:28:58,920 --> 00:29:01,560
Even if I'm not actually
related to him by blood?

376
00:29:04,320 --> 00:29:06,960
Bloodlines aren't as important
as one's actions.

377
00:29:07,560 --> 00:29:09,120
And everything you've done

378
00:29:09,200 --> 00:29:11,680
proves that Grandpa
chose the right person.

379
00:29:19,280 --> 00:29:20,480
Thank you.

380
00:29:23,160 --> 00:29:24,240
Of course.

381
00:29:46,560 --> 00:29:49,400
THATRIPAN TYCOON AND WIFE
KILLED IN RAINY MOUNTAIN CAR CRASH

382
00:29:59,600 --> 00:30:03,320
- Is this for me, Sasi?
- Yes.

383
00:30:04,280 --> 00:30:05,800
It's to give you strength.

384
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:15,640
I know how much pain you're in,

385
00:30:16,280 --> 00:30:19,280
losing both of your parents like this.

386
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:21,840
But I want you to be strong

387
00:30:22,440 --> 00:30:25,120
and find a way to get through this.

388
00:30:29,120 --> 00:30:30,960
And will you stay by my side

389
00:30:33,080 --> 00:30:35,240
so we can get through it together?

390
00:30:35,320 --> 00:30:36,800
Of course I will.

391
00:30:47,240 --> 00:30:49,000
Finally, I'm the only one left.

392
00:30:55,080 --> 00:30:56,840
Sasi, what are you doing right now?

393
00:31:05,640 --> 00:31:07,200
KOPI TIAM

394
00:31:19,800 --> 00:31:20,840
This is excellent.

395
00:31:21,400 --> 00:31:23,920
I didn't expect to find
such rich coffee in Phuket.

396
00:31:24,840 --> 00:31:28,160
In Bangkok, everyone's resorted
to mixing with roasted tamarind seeds.

397
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:30,000
War makes everything scarce.

398
00:31:30,840 --> 00:31:34,000
Kopi Tiam was the first coffee shop
in Phuket.

399
00:31:34,080 --> 00:31:36,200
It's only natural
they'd maintain their standards.

400
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:38,640
We moved here at the same time,

401
00:31:38,720 --> 00:31:40,080
yet you know much more than I do.

402
00:31:44,520 --> 00:31:46,000
It's been over 20 days.

403
00:31:47,120 --> 00:31:48,560
Any new leads?

404
00:31:50,200 --> 00:31:51,400
Not yet.

405
00:31:53,120 --> 00:31:54,600
And who do you suspect?

406
00:31:56,840 --> 00:31:58,520
Everyone at Som Song Saeng House.

407
00:31:59,680 --> 00:32:02,560
All of Wild Bull's relatives
can't be trusted.

408
00:32:02,640 --> 00:32:04,800
The only good one is Fuangfah.

409
00:32:04,880 --> 00:32:06,120
The rest are all vultures.

410
00:32:07,600 --> 00:32:10,320
If you told me one of them
was working with Black Beard,

411
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:11,680
I'd believe it in a heartbeat.

412
00:32:15,440 --> 00:32:17,040
But I've found an ally.

413
00:32:18,480 --> 00:32:19,360
Who?

414
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:21,280
Colonel Nakamura.

415
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:28,520
The Japanese have suffered
because of Black Beard as well.

416
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:30,720
We might be able to pull him to our side.

417
00:32:31,400 --> 00:32:32,360
That sounds perfect.

418
00:32:33,320 --> 00:32:34,440
He could be a huge help to us.

419
00:32:35,280 --> 00:32:38,040
In that case, you take it from here.

420
00:32:38,120 --> 00:32:39,480
I'm calling it quits.

421
00:32:39,560 --> 00:32:40,600
Hey.

422
00:32:40,680 --> 00:32:42,680
Why are you abandoning me all of a sudden?

423
00:32:43,280 --> 00:32:44,560
It's necessary.

424
00:32:44,640 --> 00:32:47,000
Those nightmare relatives
are already conspiring to sue me.

425
00:32:47,080 --> 00:32:48,440
I can't hold them off.

426
00:32:49,280 --> 00:32:51,880
If they start digging, I'll have to run.

427
00:32:51,960 --> 00:32:52,880
I've done all I can.

428
00:32:52,960 --> 00:32:53,920
You can't do that.

429
00:32:59,160 --> 00:33:02,120
You are the one closest to the suspect.

430
00:33:02,720 --> 00:33:06,160
If you won't help me,
how am I supposed to continue?

431
00:33:06,240 --> 00:33:08,040
You know exactly who I am,

432
00:33:08,120 --> 00:33:10,160
and right now, I have nothing.

433
00:33:10,240 --> 00:33:13,040
If they sue, I won't even have
the money to hire a lawyer.

434
00:33:15,520 --> 00:33:16,920
What if I were to help you?

435
00:33:20,880 --> 00:33:21,840
How?

436
00:33:22,440 --> 00:33:25,520
I'll provide a lawyer
and handle all the costs.

437
00:33:26,320 --> 00:33:27,280
If the truth comes out,

438
00:33:27,360 --> 00:33:30,800
I'll just claim you were working
undercover to catch Black Beard.

439
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:33,480
You won't face any charges.

440
00:33:44,880 --> 00:33:46,840
Is this a lawsuit or an ancient epic?

441
00:33:46,920 --> 00:33:49,200
- It's incredibly thick.
- Are you afraid?

442
00:33:49,800 --> 00:33:50,680
If so,

443
00:33:50,760 --> 00:33:54,160
then get your ass out
of Som Song Saeng House right now.

444
00:33:54,240 --> 00:33:56,720
No. If I leave,
how am I supposed to make a living?

445
00:33:58,000 --> 00:33:58,920
You shameless bastard.

446
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:00,240
Guilty as charged.

447
00:34:01,240 --> 00:34:03,520
But the fact that you keep threatening me

448
00:34:03,600 --> 00:34:06,040
without actually filing the lawsuit…
It's obvious, isn't it?

449
00:34:06,120 --> 00:34:08,320
You know you can't win.

450
00:34:14,520 --> 00:34:16,280
As the lawyer stated,

451
00:34:16,880 --> 00:34:19,040
I am the legal heir.

452
00:34:19,120 --> 00:34:21,960
No one has the right to disqualify me,

453
00:34:22,040 --> 00:34:23,320
blood relation or not.

454
00:34:26,199 --> 00:34:27,239
Not as dumb as you look.

455
00:34:29,120 --> 00:34:30,440
But do you have any idea

456
00:34:31,120 --> 00:34:34,199
what will happen
once the legal battle starts?

457
00:34:34,960 --> 00:34:37,199
Vijarn, enlighten him.

458
00:34:37,280 --> 00:34:39,960
Yes, madam. Excuse me.

459
00:34:40,040 --> 00:34:42,520
If a lawsuit is officially filed,

460
00:34:42,600 --> 00:34:45,000
all inheritance transfers must be frozen

461
00:34:45,639 --> 00:34:47,120
until the case is settled.

462
00:34:47,960 --> 00:34:50,040
Furthermore, the central allowance

463
00:34:50,120 --> 00:34:52,040
will be provided only to Miss Rajit.

464
00:34:52,120 --> 00:34:54,040
Yours will be withheld indefinitely.

465
00:34:56,840 --> 00:34:58,240
Go ahead and do your duty, Lawyer.

466
00:35:04,280 --> 00:35:05,200
Fuang.

467
00:35:07,840 --> 00:35:09,360
Please don't, Pae.

468
00:35:09,960 --> 00:35:13,200
What? Are you taking his side over mine?

469
00:35:13,280 --> 00:35:14,640
Come on.

470
00:35:18,520 --> 00:35:21,080
I'm so sorry, Thatri.

471
00:35:22,280 --> 00:35:24,200
But I know the truth.

472
00:35:41,080 --> 00:35:43,920
I've known since before
Uncle Som passed away.

473
00:35:44,520 --> 00:35:46,880
He sent someone
to look into Aunt Suang's life

474
00:35:49,240 --> 00:35:51,280
and found out
that your family's financials

475
00:35:51,360 --> 00:35:52,760
aren't great.

476
00:35:55,040 --> 00:35:56,960
Though you're not in debt,

477
00:35:57,040 --> 00:35:59,320
you're living hand-to-mouth.

478
00:35:59,400 --> 00:36:01,680
A long legal battle

479
00:36:01,760 --> 00:36:03,520
would be devastating for you.

480
00:36:07,400 --> 00:36:10,720
What if you accepted a lump sum
in exchange for renouncing the fortune?

481
00:36:12,080 --> 00:36:13,800
What would you say?

482
00:36:16,040 --> 00:36:18,680
Listen, you're not stupid.

483
00:36:18,760 --> 00:36:20,200
You must realize

484
00:36:20,280 --> 00:36:22,840
that hiring a lawyer
is pocket change to me.

485
00:36:24,040 --> 00:36:25,640
I can drag this out

486
00:36:25,720 --> 00:36:28,440
for 20 or 30 years
without breaking a sweat.

487
00:36:29,560 --> 00:36:30,840
But you?

488
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:33,960
You'll be bankrupt within a year.

489
00:36:35,600 --> 00:36:36,720
Take the deal.

490
00:36:36,800 --> 00:36:39,120
Consider this my act of mercy.

491
00:36:42,320 --> 00:36:44,320
Thank you for your mercy.

492
00:36:44,400 --> 00:36:46,440
But I think

493
00:36:46,520 --> 00:36:49,600
you should keep your money
for your funeral.

494
00:36:49,680 --> 00:36:50,800
Don't offer it to me.

495
00:36:54,680 --> 00:36:56,240
I've made my decision.

496
00:36:56,320 --> 00:36:57,240
I'm fighting this.

497
00:36:57,320 --> 00:37:00,280
Even if it leads
to bankruptcy, I will fight.

498
00:37:00,360 --> 00:37:02,960
That's my final word.
You're getting on my nerves.

499
00:37:07,960 --> 00:37:08,800
Pae. Sister.

500
00:37:08,880 --> 00:37:10,040
- Calm down.
- I'm doing this all for you,

501
00:37:10,120 --> 00:37:11,320
Wild Bull.

502
00:37:12,160 --> 00:37:13,080
Calm down, sister.

503
00:37:13,840 --> 00:37:16,120
- Ugh!
- Keep it down. Don't scream.

504
00:37:19,680 --> 00:37:22,560
- The horse is ready, Miss Rajit.
- Thank you.

505
00:37:37,200 --> 00:37:38,560
You keep horses here too?

506
00:37:38,640 --> 00:37:41,200
Yes, sir. We use them to check
on the rubber plantation.

507
00:37:41,280 --> 00:37:43,720
The paths are steep and full of potholes.

508
00:37:43,800 --> 00:37:46,120
Cars can't make it through.
Horses are the only way.

509
00:37:53,640 --> 00:37:54,600
Do you know how to ride?

510
00:37:55,440 --> 00:37:56,440
Want me to take you?

511
00:37:58,640 --> 00:38:00,000
Look at my outfit.

512
00:38:02,560 --> 00:38:03,720
I certainly don't need help

513
00:38:03,800 --> 00:38:05,720
just to ride a horse.

514
00:38:38,360 --> 00:38:39,840
Nice outfit, by the way.

515
00:38:44,040 --> 00:38:45,800
They call this "all bark, no bite".

516
00:38:46,560 --> 00:38:49,040
Seriously though,
how much for that outfit?

517
00:38:50,280 --> 00:38:51,920
That's enough, Uncle Ree.

518
00:38:52,520 --> 00:38:55,040
Just a little bit more.
I'll stop once we reach the plantation.

519
00:38:55,760 --> 00:38:57,040
Uncle Ree.

520
00:38:58,800 --> 00:38:59,840
Hey,

521
00:39:01,360 --> 00:39:02,720
I may tease you,

522
00:39:02,800 --> 00:39:05,080
but I truly admire your dedication.

523
00:39:05,160 --> 00:39:07,920
I didn't think a kid like you
would take work so seriously.

524
00:39:08,000 --> 00:39:10,000
It's exactly why

525
00:39:10,080 --> 00:39:11,880
I have to prove them wrong.

526
00:39:11,960 --> 00:39:14,080
I won't let anyone say

527
00:39:14,160 --> 00:39:15,840
I just squandered my inheritance

528
00:39:15,920 --> 00:39:17,320
because I couldn't manage it.

529
00:39:27,760 --> 00:39:29,920
Uncle Ree!

530
00:39:31,560 --> 00:39:33,560
Help me! Uncle Ree!

531
00:39:47,080 --> 00:39:49,640
Uncle Ree! Please help me!

532
00:39:52,440 --> 00:39:54,320
Please help me! Uncle Ree!

533
00:39:54,400 --> 00:39:58,040
Make it stop! Uncle Ree!

534
00:39:59,800 --> 00:40:01,160
Rajit!

535
00:40:06,720 --> 00:40:07,640
Stop!

536
00:40:13,080 --> 00:40:14,840
- Uncle Ree!
- Rajit!

537
00:40:15,440 --> 00:40:17,640
- Reach out to me.
- How?

538
00:40:17,720 --> 00:40:20,560
How?

539
00:41:20,880 --> 00:41:22,240
Rajit.

540
00:41:24,400 --> 00:41:25,320
Rajit.

541
00:41:26,520 --> 00:41:27,640
Rajit.

542
00:41:28,840 --> 00:41:29,880
Rajit.

543
00:41:30,440 --> 00:41:31,520
Rajit.

544
00:41:33,440 --> 00:41:34,560
Rajit.

545
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:41,360
Something's happened to Miss Rajit?
How do you know, Nid?

546
00:41:41,440 --> 00:41:43,920
Loy Lom, the horse Miss Rajit took out,

547
00:41:44,000 --> 00:41:47,080
just returned alone.
Miss Rajit was nowhere to be seen.

548
00:41:47,160 --> 00:41:48,480
And Mr. Thatri, who went with her,

549
00:41:49,080 --> 00:41:50,320
hasn't returned either.

550
00:41:50,400 --> 00:41:52,080
I'm afraid something might have happened.

551
00:41:55,520 --> 00:41:57,000
It would be for the best

552
00:41:57,080 --> 00:41:58,720
if something did happen to them.

553
00:42:00,000 --> 00:42:01,880
Don't say things like that, Pae.

554
00:42:02,440 --> 00:42:03,320
Why?

555
00:42:03,400 --> 00:42:05,920
Do you think I actually care
about that girl?

556
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:07,840
And as for that man,

557
00:42:07,920 --> 00:42:09,480
it'd be better if he just stayed dead.

558
00:42:13,160 --> 00:42:15,120
Send some men to look for them, Vijarn.

559
00:42:15,200 --> 00:42:18,400
If something happened,
they'll be on the trail to the plantation.

560
00:42:18,480 --> 00:42:19,480
Yes, Miss Fuangfah.

561
00:42:19,560 --> 00:42:20,840
Nid,

562
00:42:20,920 --> 00:42:23,400
gather everyone and search
for Miss Rajit immediately.

563
00:42:23,480 --> 00:42:25,760
- I'll go find more help.
- Yes, sir.

564
00:42:46,400 --> 00:42:47,520
How are you feeling?

565
00:42:48,200 --> 00:42:49,600
You were out for quite a while.

566
00:42:53,080 --> 00:42:55,640
Now, tell me… What's your name?

567
00:42:58,720 --> 00:43:00,920
Uncle Ree, are you alright?

568
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:02,520
My name is Rajit, of course.

569
00:43:03,720 --> 00:43:06,600
Since you're being this annoying,
you're clearly fine.

570
00:43:13,400 --> 00:43:15,080
Did you do all this yourself?

571
00:43:15,160 --> 00:43:16,520
Do you see anyone else here?

572
00:43:17,400 --> 00:43:18,280
What a strange question.

573
00:43:19,440 --> 00:43:22,440
I was complimenting you
on your survival skills.

574
00:43:23,000 --> 00:43:24,280
Why do you have to be sarcastic?

575
00:43:32,360 --> 00:43:34,880
I spend a lot of time in the wilderness.
This is easy for me.

576
00:43:37,760 --> 00:43:40,200
Thank you, but I'm not hungry yet.

577
00:43:40,880 --> 00:43:43,520
Eat, even if you're not hungry. It's late.

578
00:43:43,600 --> 00:43:45,520
It'll be dark when we reach the house.

579
00:43:45,600 --> 00:43:48,520
If we get lost and have to camp out,

580
00:43:49,200 --> 00:43:50,680
you'll regret being hungry at night.

581
00:43:53,360 --> 00:43:54,600
Thank you.

582
00:43:59,680 --> 00:44:02,920
The family you mowed lawns for
must have taken you into the woods often.

583
00:44:03,000 --> 00:44:04,920
That's where you got the skills.

584
00:44:06,360 --> 00:44:08,360
Would it kill you to eat in silence?

585
00:44:09,160 --> 00:44:11,440
I should've ridden back home alone.

586
00:44:24,960 --> 00:44:25,920
It's burning!

587
00:44:26,680 --> 00:44:28,080
Serves you right.

588
00:44:29,080 --> 00:44:31,480
Maybe your tongue
should've stayed blistered for a few days.

589
00:44:42,080 --> 00:44:43,000
Serves you right.

590
00:44:43,080 --> 00:44:45,960
Maybe your tongue
should've stayed blistered for a few days.

591
00:44:54,960 --> 00:44:56,760
- Miss Rajit.
- Mr. Thatri.

592
00:44:56,840 --> 00:44:58,200
- Miss Rajit.
- Mr. Thatri.

593
00:44:58,280 --> 00:44:59,720
- Miss Rajit.
- Mr. Thatri.

594
00:45:00,840 --> 00:45:02,280
Miss Rajit.

595
00:45:04,400 --> 00:45:05,760
Miss Rajit, can you hear me?

596
00:45:06,800 --> 00:45:07,760
We're almost at the plantation.

597
00:45:07,840 --> 00:45:09,680
There's still no sign of them, Mr. Vijarn.

598
00:45:09,760 --> 00:45:11,080
What should we do now?

599
00:45:13,320 --> 00:45:15,080
Keep searching. Don't stop.

600
00:45:15,640 --> 00:45:18,040
- Let's go.
- Maybe the horse bolted off the main path?

601
00:45:20,800 --> 00:45:21,840
How would you know that?

602
00:45:22,520 --> 00:45:25,920
Just a guess. From Som Song Saeng House
to the plantation,

603
00:45:26,000 --> 00:45:27,200
there's only one road.

604
00:45:27,920 --> 00:45:30,000
If they weren't off-trail,
we would've found them.

605
00:45:31,680 --> 00:45:33,160
Wai has a point.

606
00:45:33,240 --> 00:45:34,680
Loy Lom came back alone.

607
00:45:34,760 --> 00:45:36,520
It's possible he got spooked

608
00:45:36,600 --> 00:45:38,200
and bolted off the trail.

609
00:45:38,280 --> 00:45:40,800
Once he calmed down,
he just headed back to the stable.

610
00:45:42,240 --> 00:45:43,560
But if that's the case,

611
00:45:43,640 --> 00:45:46,000
Miss Rajit could have been
thrown off anywhere.

612
00:45:46,760 --> 00:45:49,240
We're in trouble. She could be anywhere.

613
00:45:56,200 --> 00:45:58,320
We must find her.

614
00:45:58,400 --> 00:46:00,760
Everyone, fan out.

615
00:46:00,840 --> 00:46:03,760
I'll reward anyone who finds her.
Move out, now.

616
00:46:04,360 --> 00:46:07,040
Let's go. Miss Rajit.

617
00:46:08,480 --> 00:46:10,520
Miss Rajit.

618
00:46:11,680 --> 00:46:13,600
- Mr. Thatri.
- Miss Rajit.

619
00:46:13,680 --> 00:46:14,640
- Miss Rajit.
- Mr. Thatri.

620
00:46:14,720 --> 00:46:15,720
Miss Rajit.

621
00:46:16,440 --> 00:46:17,880
- Miss Rajit.
- Mr. Thatri.

622
00:46:22,440 --> 00:46:25,040
I thought you weren't hungry.
You cleared out every yam in the forest.

623
00:46:25,120 --> 00:46:26,880
That's how it is with growing kids.

624
00:46:34,280 --> 00:46:35,760
- Help!
- Rajit!

625
00:46:35,840 --> 00:46:38,160
Uncle Ree! Please help me!

626
00:46:44,640 --> 00:46:47,440
Listen, I won't beat around the bush.

627
00:46:47,520 --> 00:46:49,360
Do you have any enemies?

628
00:46:49,440 --> 00:46:51,480
You think the horse bolting

629
00:46:53,040 --> 00:46:54,720
was someone's doing?

630
00:46:55,960 --> 00:46:58,600
- You're quick.
- If I were slow,

631
00:46:58,680 --> 00:47:01,640
I'd have been dead the day
I took the Adisuan name.

632
00:47:01,720 --> 00:47:04,360
Fair point.
I've only been here a few days,

633
00:47:04,440 --> 00:47:06,080
and I'm already exhausted.

634
00:47:08,880 --> 00:47:10,600
I don't have any specific enemies.

635
00:47:10,680 --> 00:47:14,400
But if you're asking who I suspect,
everyone is a possibility.

636
00:47:15,160 --> 00:47:16,520
You've seen them yourself.

637
00:47:17,680 --> 00:47:18,560
That's true.

638
00:47:21,480 --> 00:47:23,040
No sign of them yet?

639
00:47:24,040 --> 00:47:25,480
Are they dead yet?

640
00:47:26,200 --> 00:47:28,440
Sister, we're talking about
human lives here.

641
00:47:29,880 --> 00:47:32,520
Besides, even if something
happened to those two,

642
00:47:32,600 --> 00:47:34,640
the inheritance
wouldn't come to us anyway.

643
00:47:35,360 --> 00:47:38,720
Don't forget. We don't share
any blood with Uncle Som.

644
00:47:40,480 --> 00:47:41,880
I'm well aware.

645
00:47:41,960 --> 00:47:43,520
But if they're dead,

646
00:47:43,600 --> 00:47:46,040
it would buy us time
to move things around.

647
00:47:46,120 --> 00:47:49,800
By the time their distant kin
show up to claim the estate,

648
00:47:51,480 --> 00:47:53,480
there won't be a single cash left.

649
00:47:54,840 --> 00:47:56,200
Is this really how you feel?

650
00:47:56,840 --> 00:47:57,880
Hey, you.

651
00:47:57,960 --> 00:48:00,360
If you don't want
a piece of the pie, then shut up.

652
00:48:00,440 --> 00:48:02,360
I've worked myself
to the bone for Uncle Som.

653
00:48:02,440 --> 00:48:05,080
Without me, would the Adisuan
even be this rich?

654
00:48:05,160 --> 00:48:07,720
I won't stand by and let strangers
reap what I sowed.

655
00:48:08,880 --> 00:48:11,120
Uncle Som's fortune

656
00:48:11,200 --> 00:48:12,880
belongs to me.

657
00:48:17,960 --> 00:48:19,080
Can I ask you something?

658
00:48:20,880 --> 00:48:23,440
Why did Uncle Som have you change
your last name to Adisuan?

659
00:48:23,520 --> 00:48:25,920
Doing that is like putting
a target on your back.

660
00:48:26,640 --> 00:48:27,920
It was necessary.

661
00:48:28,640 --> 00:48:31,160
My mother passed away when I was six.

662
00:48:32,240 --> 00:48:33,920
My father remarried,

663
00:48:34,000 --> 00:48:37,000
I didn't get along
with my stepmother or her children.

664
00:48:37,920 --> 00:48:40,560
My grandfather took pity on me,
so he took me in

665
00:48:41,120 --> 00:48:43,920
and changed my surname to Adisuan,

666
00:48:44,000 --> 00:48:47,560
so my father and his relatives
couldn't interfere with my life.

667
00:48:48,640 --> 00:48:52,200
The Adisuan family needed an heir
since my grandpa had no children.

668
00:48:58,800 --> 00:49:00,200
A Cinderella story, then.

669
00:49:02,760 --> 00:49:06,280
Just missing the pumpkin carriage
and the Prince Charming.

670
00:49:07,800 --> 00:49:10,040
I wouldn't mind the pumpkin carriage,

671
00:49:10,680 --> 00:49:12,480
but I have no need for a prince.

672
00:49:13,520 --> 00:49:14,880
Hold on.

673
00:49:14,960 --> 00:49:17,240
Do you not need one,
or do you just not have one?

674
00:49:17,320 --> 00:49:19,120
There's a big difference, you know.

675
00:49:19,880 --> 00:49:22,920
You think I've never had anyone?
I did have someone.

676
00:49:27,480 --> 00:49:29,400
Kajorn and I love each other.

677
00:49:30,520 --> 00:49:31,960
The man I love…

678
00:49:33,960 --> 00:49:35,840
and my dearest friend?

679
00:49:35,920 --> 00:49:39,240
Love doesn't leave room for three.

680
00:49:41,640 --> 00:49:43,800
Kajorn chose me,

681
00:49:44,640 --> 00:49:46,120
and I love him.

682
00:49:53,920 --> 00:49:55,880
I have plenty of men chasing after me,

683
00:49:55,960 --> 00:49:57,840
but I find it all quite pointless.

684
00:49:57,920 --> 00:50:00,760
Why should an educated woman
who can support herself

685
00:50:00,840 --> 00:50:02,480
bother with men?

686
00:50:03,880 --> 00:50:05,320
What about you, Uncle Ree?

687
00:50:05,400 --> 00:50:09,280
I remember our first meeting.

688
00:50:09,360 --> 00:50:11,640
You had the nerve
to claim I was stalking you.

689
00:50:12,280 --> 00:50:13,480
You're full of yourself.

690
00:50:14,400 --> 00:50:15,400
Can't help it.

691
00:50:15,480 --> 00:50:17,240
I've had experiences like that before.

692
00:50:17,320 --> 00:50:19,800
Experiences with women stalking you?

693
00:50:19,880 --> 00:50:22,640
Forgive me, Uncle Ree, relative or not,

694
00:50:22,720 --> 00:50:24,680
but that sounds like a total lie.

695
00:50:25,280 --> 00:50:26,800
I think someone like you

696
00:50:28,480 --> 00:50:30,360
should find at least
one person who loves you first.

697
00:50:32,160 --> 00:50:34,680
Who says I haven't?
I actually did have someone.

698
00:50:39,040 --> 00:50:41,080
I won't beat around the bush.

699
00:50:42,080 --> 00:50:45,120
I want you to break off the engagement.

700
00:50:48,880 --> 00:50:50,360
I'm just so sorry.

701
00:50:56,760 --> 00:50:58,320
Goodbye,

702
00:50:59,040 --> 00:51:00,160
Sasi.

703
00:51:12,560 --> 00:51:14,960
I've broken plenty of hearts in my time.

704
00:51:17,160 --> 00:51:20,760
But lately, I've grown weary
of the bad karma, so I decided to stop.

705
00:51:26,680 --> 00:51:28,320
- Mr. Thatri.
- Miss Rajit.

706
00:51:28,400 --> 00:51:30,440
- Mr. Thatri, can you hear me?
- Miss Rajit.

707
00:51:30,960 --> 00:51:31,920
- Mr. Thatri.
- Miss Rajit.

708
00:51:32,000 --> 00:51:33,240
Miss Rajit.

709
00:51:33,320 --> 00:51:34,760
Mr. Thatri.

710
00:51:34,840 --> 00:51:37,160
Miss Rajit.

711
00:51:37,240 --> 00:51:38,200
Miss Rajit.

712
00:51:38,280 --> 00:51:39,840
- Mr. Thatri.
- Miss Rajit, can you hear me?

713
00:51:39,920 --> 00:51:41,080
If you can, please shout out.

714
00:51:41,160 --> 00:51:42,800
Mr. Thatri, can you hear me?

715
00:51:44,680 --> 00:51:47,040
In a forest this vast,
we'll never find them.

716
00:51:47,680 --> 00:51:49,160
We're likely to get stranded.

717
00:51:49,240 --> 00:51:52,320
It's nearly nightfall.
I think we should head back.

718
00:51:53,000 --> 00:51:55,240
Keep searching until Miss Rajit is found.

719
00:51:55,320 --> 00:51:57,200
If we don't find her,

720
00:51:58,240 --> 00:51:59,640
nobody is going home!

721
00:52:05,360 --> 00:52:06,520
Mr. Thatri.

722
00:52:06,600 --> 00:52:08,240
- Miss Rajit.
- Mr. Thatri.

723
00:52:20,240 --> 00:52:21,720
Are you sure you're okay?

724
00:52:23,200 --> 00:52:24,560
I'm fine.

725
00:52:29,840 --> 00:52:31,840
The clouds are gone, the stars are out.

726
00:52:32,680 --> 00:52:34,040
Let's get back home.

727
00:52:35,120 --> 00:52:35,960
Come on.

728
00:52:58,400 --> 00:53:01,640
What are you waiting for?
Do you plan on sleeping here?

729
00:53:02,800 --> 00:53:04,760
The stars are beautiful.

730
00:53:05,400 --> 00:53:08,880
I had no idea the stars out here
would be this breathtaking at night.

731
00:53:22,880 --> 00:53:24,400
Uncle Ree.

732
00:53:24,480 --> 00:53:26,440
Is that the Milky Way over there?

733
00:53:29,720 --> 00:53:30,760
Yeah.

734
00:54:33,240 --> 00:54:34,480
There's dirt on your head.

735
00:54:38,320 --> 00:54:39,680
Oh, really?

736
00:55:23,640 --> 00:55:26,040
Stay here. I'll go check it out myself.

737
00:56:16,760 --> 00:56:18,840
Miss Rajit.

738
00:56:25,120 --> 00:56:26,560
Wai?

739
00:56:26,640 --> 00:56:29,400
Miss Rajit.

740
00:56:29,480 --> 00:56:32,480
There you are.
I've been searching everywhere.

741
00:56:32,560 --> 00:56:34,080
Where is Mr. Thatri?

742
00:56:37,600 --> 00:56:39,080
Oh, Nid.

743
00:56:39,160 --> 00:56:40,360
You came looking for us?

744
00:56:40,960 --> 00:56:41,920
Yes, sir.

745
00:56:42,840 --> 00:56:46,040
We've been searching for you all day.
I'm glad you're both unharmed.

746
00:56:46,800 --> 00:56:47,920
I'll go inform the others,

747
00:56:48,520 --> 00:56:49,640
so we can head back.

748
00:57:03,280 --> 00:57:05,200
Let's head back right away, then.

749
00:57:12,560 --> 00:57:14,320
- Who does that room belong to?
- Wai, sir.

750
00:57:15,200 --> 00:57:17,360
Wai, just turn yourself in to the police.

751
00:57:22,120 --> 00:57:24,160
White flowers, to say I'm sorry.

752
00:57:24,240 --> 00:57:27,520
Her ex is back to win her over.
She might actually be happy about it.

753
00:57:27,600 --> 00:57:30,200
- But that man--
- You seem very concerned about her.

754
00:57:30,960 --> 00:57:32,360
I have feelings for you.

755
00:57:33,600 --> 00:57:35,520
- Know your place.
- Stop!

756
00:57:35,600 --> 00:57:37,760
A full-blown war just to win your heart.

757
00:57:37,840 --> 00:57:38,960
You must be so proud.

758
00:57:42,480 --> 00:57:43,600
<i>They're getting bolder every day.</i>

759
00:57:43,680 --> 00:57:44,680
<i>Raiding cargo ships</i>

760
00:57:45,280 --> 00:57:47,360
<i>and now coming ashore</i>
<i>to terrorize and kill the locals.</i>

761
00:57:47,440 --> 00:57:48,720
How can we take them down?

762
00:57:48,800 --> 00:57:50,280
We don't even know where they are.

763
00:58:18,960 --> 00:58:20,880
Subtitle translation by:
Khathathong Thongtumlueng
